style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To change the attributes of a gas cloud simply
double-click it. This will display an editing panel at the right of the scr=
een.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Here you can change t=
he gas
clouds name or alter its size.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Scenery bonuses and r=
esearch
bonuses may also be changed here.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You can also alter th=
e amount
of radiation emitted by the gas cloud in any of the three spectrums: solar,
microwave or X-ray.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You may choose to add=
 or
remove gas resources at the gas cloud. Resources can also have their quanti=
ty
and abundance levels changed. Click in the &#8220;Qty&#8221; or &#8220;%&#8=
221;
columns of the resources grid to change these values.</span></p>

